            <title>[JENA-1902] Jena riot command printing errors to stdout not stderr</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JENA-1902</link>
                <project id="12311220" key="JENA">Apache Jena</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Staring with Jena 3.15.0 the riot command in printing warnings and errors to stdout rather than stderr. This results in invalid results if stdout is redirected to a file, as logging messages are mixed with data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux 5.4.0-31-generic Ubuntu SMP&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
