                            <comment id="17118123" author="andy.seaborne" created="Wed, 27 May 2020 21:46:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rybesh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rybesh&quot;&gt;rybesh&lt;/a&gt; &#8211; thanks for the report.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A workaround for 3.15.0 is to use the fact that you can pass in the name of a configuration file with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;// Linux and Mac:
LOGGING=-Dlog4j.configurationFile=file:log4j2.properties riot ....
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so that if there is a &lt;tt&gt;log4j2.properties&lt;/tt&gt; file in the directory where &lt;tt&gt;riot&lt;/tt&gt; is run, that will be used in place of the built-in one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Code built in settings:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/jena/blob/jena-3.15.0/jena-base/src/main/java/org/apache/jena/atlas/logging/LogCtl.java#L241&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/jena/blob/jena-3.15.0/jena-base/src/main/java/org/apache/jena/atlas/logging/LogCtl.java#L241&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shipped file with the same in it:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/jena/blob/jena-3.15.0/apache-jena/log4j2.properties&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/jena/blob/jena-3.15.0/apache-jena/log4j2.properties&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add a line in the appender.console section:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;appender.console.target = SYSTEM_ERR
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to get stderr output.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
